It is believed that the lightning rod was invented by Benjamin Franklin in 1752, although there is evidence of the existence of structures with lightning rods before this date (for example, high masts upholstered with copper near temples in Ancient Egypt, similar structures near the Temple of King Solomon in Jerusalem [4], Nevyansk tower, kites by Jacques Rom [5]). In Russia, the first lightning rods were created by M. V. Lomonosov and G. V. Richman in 1753 [6]
A description of the first method of protection against lightning appears in the yearbook "Poor Richard's Almanac." "The method is this," wrote Franklin. into the damp earth, and raise six or seven others above the highest part of the building.